Commentary.Commentary: Have to assume the wicket will be at its best on Day 1 and probably Day 2 and Pakistan need to cash in. They will be wanting to take the lead as they will be batting last. Can the big names in their XI come to the fore. England on the other hand, will once again rely on their pacers to do the job for them. However, the wicket was assisting the spinners in the first innings, will the English pacers come to the fore though again?

For Pakistan, it was hard work before Abrar Ahmed weaved his magic. The pacers did not get a lot of assistance from the wicket and they struggled to pick wickets. Abrar Ahmed though spun a web and was on course of taking all 10. However, Zahid Mahmood contributed towards the end as he helped his side clean the tail up.

England, won't be very disappointed with the score they have! It is we feel, an in-between total on a wicket which did assist the bowlers. England actually were off to a really good start. They 145 for 2 but once Root fell, it was a procession, they kept losing wickets at regular intervals. They tried to counter-attack but Pakistan always managed to break the stand which was starting to flourish. However, because of the way England batted, they have got themselves close to the 300-run mark.

It is Abrar Ahmed who leads Pakistan off the field and a standing ovation from the crowd here for him! He totally deserves it. Absolutely brilliant and he has had a dream debut. He is surely the reason for England being bowled out on Day 1 itself. He has 7 out of the 10 to fall and this game so far, is surely about him.

At the start of the match, it looked like it will be a hard, toiling day for the Pakistani bowlers as there was nothing much for the seamers but once the spinners were introduced the tides changed the direction. Abrar Ahmed would have thought about a wicket or so against the mighty English players but he was disciplined with his line and lengths and the youngsters ended with a five-fer. England on the other hand kept the counter attacking approach rolling. Ben Duckett and Ollie Pope led from the front and runs were easy to come at one stage. They added more than 100 with both scoring fifties but both fell in the process. Root and Brook didn't add much. England now have lost half of the side but still have a bit of batting left. They might tweak their approach as they look for a big score. A fascinating start to the Test. Let's hope the post-Lunch session is as entertaining as the first one. Do join us back after the break.

Hello everyone to the 2nd Test match between England and Pakistan. We are still not able to get over the extraordinary final minutes scenes at Rawalpindi. On a dead-flat pitch England scratched out a win and now lead this 3-match series. They have shown throughout that match the style they want to play, that is dominating cricket. Pakistan on the other hand had no answers to the banging they got and have no time to think much as they look to level the series here at Multan.
...DAY 1, SESSION 1...

Courage, belief and the ability to play one’s best cricket under pressure - These are the traits that have defined Ben Stokes, the cricketer, over the years. He was handed over the captaincy of the Test side some months back in the hope to imbibe some of these qualities into the Test side and the way he and his team has responded is simply astonishing. After pulling off a miraculous home summer in Test cricket, England have now started the Asian journey with a bang. The home team, Pakistan are on the back foot after being handed a shock defeat in the first Test match and with series on the line, it would be interesting to see how both teams go about their business in this second Test at Multan. The defeat in the first Test match at Rawalpindi was a shock for Pakistan because, for the most part of it, any other result than a draw seems improbable as the wicket seems as flat as any of those perfectly made express highways in the world. However, the adventurous decision to declare from Ben Stokes with a lead of 342 runs at Tea on Day 4, opened the possibilities of a win for both sides and though the pitch was favourable for batting, Pakistan crumbled under pressure in the final session of Day 5 to hand England a memorable win. The pace-duo of James Anderson and Ollie Robinson showed some tremendous skills on the final day and picked four wickets each in the final innings of a Test match. Also, in a Test where 1768 runs were scored, the third-most runs ever scored in a Test match, England managed to pick 20 wickets which surely is a commendable effort from the bowling group that has flown under the radar in recent times with England’s aggressive batting taking centrestage. Now, let’s just take a moment to talk about the batting performances in the first Test match. A total of seven centuries were scored in the match, four by English batters and three by Pakistani batters. However, the rate at which England scored runs in both innings was quite exhilarating. The debutant, Harry Brook was the standout performer in both innings with the bat while Will Jacks also made a strong impression with six wickets in the first innings and handy contributions with the bat. Pakistan also put up a big score on the board in the first innings with centuries by both their openers and Babar Azam but in the second innings, none of the batters could convert their starts into a substantial score. Pakistan are playing at home and the loss in the first Test match would be hurting them. Also, they would be hoping that spin will play a bigger part in Multan which might turn out to be the best possible way to stop this belligerent English unit. The leg-spinner Zahid Mahmood did pick up six wickets in the first Test and it would also be interesting to see what combination both teams prefer if the pitch turns out to be more conducive for spin bowling. Mark Wood is fit for England and is expected to play in this second Test match. The pressure is on Pakistan and there is no doubt that England will come out all guns blazing again. It promises to be another exciting Test match. Will this ‘Bazball’ approach take England to a famous series victory? Or will Pakistan show that they are the real Sultans of Multan? Let’s find out.

Pakistan on the other hand, need their bowling to deliver, their bowling department has not been great in the series so far but they need them to deliver now. Can they bowl England out for a cheap score or will the England batters continue their good form? We will find out.

England on the other hand, will be mighty pleased! Had they been given a lead of 79 at the start of the day, they would have taken it with open arms. It was Ollie Robinson who started it off but it was Jack Leach who was the pick for them with a four-fer. However, it was a combined bowling effort. Everyone except for Jacks who only bowled 4 overs picked a wicket at least.

We are back for the chase. A heavy roller is out there at the moment. The players are out in the middle. Mohammad Rizwan is promoted as he will open along with Abdullah Shafique. Ollie Robinson to start with the ball. Imam-ul-Haq is currently out due to a hamstring issue.

Pakistan have a mountain to climb. Time is not an issue at all but it is the form of their batters. Apart from Babar Azam and Saud Shakeel, no one has stepped up. This is the perfect time for them though. They are not yet out of the game. Still, a gettable target but need to show some heroics to level the series. The odd-balls are staying low and there is spin as well. England have more experience in their bowling and they will back themselves to win this game. Pakistan will look to go in Lunch without losing any wickets. Will it be that easy though?

Excellent bowling display from Pakistan but tell you what, England have done a good job in this first hour to score bulk of runs. They added 73 runs in no time. Pakistan need 355 runs to win the game. A big performance is needed from their batters. England started Day 3 with Ben Stokes and Harry Brook being watchful but once they got settled, boundaries were easy to buy. They were scoring runs at a very quick rate. Harry Brook went on to notch his second century of the series. However, once both fell, there was nothing from the other batters. Pakistan did well to clear the tail quickly. All 10 wickets fell to the spinners with Abrar Ahmed taking 4 wickets, 11 in total in this match.

Hello and welcome to the action of Day 3 between England and Pakistan. The visitors are in a commanding position as they have a lead of 281 runs. Another 100-150 runs and they will be happy to ask Pakistan to chase it down. Pakistan on the other hand need a few players to step up as only the debutant, Abrar is putting in a shift. They will look to rattle England as low as possible.
...Day 3, Session 1...

England played more sensibly this time than we saw in the first innings. Ben Duckett played his usual shots and notched up his second consecutive fifty. Harry Brook constructed his innings well and scored a fifty. He is looking in fine form and he along with his skipper will look to continue the good work. For Pakistan, they need wickets, wickets and wickets. We feel the first session of Day 3 will be very crucial for Pakistan. England will come out and look for runs straightaway. A score around 380-400 looks reasonable on this pitch. Still, a lot of hard work has to be done for Pakistan to stay in this game. Join us on Day 3 at 10.05 IST (4.35 am GMT) and earlier for the coverage. Till then, cheers.

So, Day 2 belongs to the visitors. England will be really happy. A lead of 281 with 5 wickets left. They are in pole position to win this game. Pakistan had their moments but not enough to get on top of the game. Pakistan were in a good position at one stage with Babar Azam and Saud Shakeel both getting their fifties and their partnership of 91 looked very promising but once Babar fell, the doors opened for England to scalp some more wickets quickly. Saud Shakeel fell later and no one other than these two made a huge impact to their innings. Jack Leach claimed 4 wickets and Pakistan gave away a lead of 79.

...DAY 2, SESSION 3...

Pakistan have done well to take three wickets but their job is not over yet as they will look to take the remaining wickets as soon as possible. Abrar Ahmed has now 9 wickets in his first match. He will play a key role in the final session while others have to motor around him. An interesting last session awaits. Stay tuned.

Both teams will be happy with the session but the visitors will be a touch happier as they stretch their lead to 168 runs. It was Ben Duckett who is negotiating the spin well yet again. He along with Root looked very settled but Root fell to Abrar Ahmed and the 50-odd runs stand was broken. England have a lot of time left and have enough batting left to stretch their lead more.

Right then! England win the series but there is one more match to go. We move to Karachi for the last match. Join us on the 17th of this month at 1030 IST (0500 GMT) and earlier for the build up. Till then, cheers!

Ben Stokes, the captain of England says the conditions here was different but it was another fantastic game and it was great to be a part of. Mentions it seemed a tricky wicket and he praises the seamers for the way they bowled. Congratulates Abrar but says it was good to score against him. Ends by saying he looks around and sees who is the best option to give him a wicket and he turns to them.

Babar Azam, the skipper of Pakistan says they weren't upto the mark with the bat in the first innings. They fought back well in the second innings but could not finish on top. States they have a plan, they had a couple of good partnerships but in the end, they did not finish well. Adds it is a dream start for Abrar and it is good for the team. Ends by saying they are looking forward to the next game and hope to win it.

Harry Brook wins the Player of the Match award. Brook says he tried to learn from his mistake and tried to be a little less aggressive and still put pressure on the bowlers. Adds they knew it would turn and they weren't surprised but they did not bat as they wanted to in the first game. Mentions they just wanted to play with intent and put pressure on the bowler.
...Presentation coming up...

In reply, Pakistan were in a good position when Azam and Shakeel were batting but then came the Leach show. From 142 for 2, Pakistan were bowled out for 202, giving a lead of over 70 to England. Leach finished with four while Root and Wood took two apiece. It was the Harry Brook show for England, in their second innings. As his ton helped them stretch the lead to over 350 and that really proved to be a vital ton as Pakistan just lost by a narrow margin. Not to forget the innings from Ben Duckett and Ben Stokes. Pakistan were in the chase for a long time but lost wickets at the wrong time.

This game though has swung from one side to another right from Day 1. After electing to bat, England were in a brilliant position as they were 2 down for around 150 but then were bowled out for 281. Abrar Ahmed on debut was the star for Pakistan as he ended with a seven-fer.

It was the seamers who did the job for them yet again. Wood in particular, he was the star for the visitors. The game was drifting away from them when Mohammad Nawaz and Saud Shakeel were batting but Wood got them both in quick succession, he also got Zahid Mahmood and it was Robinson who sealed the deal with the last wicket. Salman did fight but he just kept running out of partners.
That is a famous win for England! 3 and a half days of hard fought cricket and it is England who finish on top and also bag the series. Top, top performance from them.

The review is taken but as expected in vain. England win by 26 runs.

...DAY 4, SESSION 2...

Pakistan still need 64 runs but the only known batter out there is Salman. He will be under tremendous pressure. England on the other hand need three wickets to seal the series. We feel the next session will give us the results. Join us back at 1310 IST (0740 GMT) for the second session.

A huge, huge session for England. It was Pakistan who bossed for most of the time but the last three overs which included the wicket of Mohammad Nawaz and Saud Shakeel has turned the tide in England's favor again. Two balls down the leg side which could be avoided but the Pakistani batters went after it. Before that, Pakistan were motoring very nicely, both Nawaz and Shakeel were calm and rotating the strike. However, England believed that the wicket is just around the corner. Mark Wood was introduced and the pacer took both big wickets.

The equation is simple, Pakistan need another 157 runs and England need to pick the remaining two wickets. It is all about one partnership for the hosts whereas for England, they'll be hoping they can keep striking on regular intervals like they have been doing. Will it end 1-1 or will England seal the series.
... DAY 4, SESSION 1 ..

Now Pakistan bat deep but their batting is quite fragile, they would know one more big partnership is all they need to put England under huge pressure. For England, they will come out all fresh on Day 4 and also with the second new ball available in a few overs, they will believe they can record a famous win. Do join us to what promises to be an enthralling 4th and also could well be the last day of the Test. The action begins at 1015 IST (0515 GMT). The build-up begins a lot earlier. Till then, take care and goodbye!

It has been a day of fight backs. After bowling out England earlier in the day, Pakistan began really well with the bat. It was Rizwan who opened due to an injury to Imam and he along with Abdullah Shafique gave the hosts a good start. However, things changed immediately after Lunch as Pakistan lost three in no time and were pushed on the back foot. Saud and Imam though then put up a 100-plus stand with both scoring half tons to turn the tide in their side's favor. Pakistan surely would have ended the day on top had they not lost Imam but it was Leach who had the last laugh by getting the left-hander late in the day.

Well, the umpires yet again feel the light is not good enough to continue and off the players and the umpires go! THAT SHOULD BE STUMPS! This game is brilliantly poised for Day 4! Pakistan need 157 and England need 6 wickets. Probably England will feel they have the upper hand but we feel, Pakistan have a really good chance here.

OUT! BOWLED! Beauty from Robinson! What a delivery! Ollie Robinson gets Babar Azam for the second time in this game. Babar Azam just like Rizwan is shell-shocked. The big wicket for England. They have really turned up after Lunch. Ask them what they had. Ollie Robinson steams in and serves a length ball, outside off, this one lands and nips back in sharply, might have hit one of the cracks. Babar Azam sees and then shoulders arms to it but the ball deviates and hits the stumps. He just watches the pitch. A late, late movement and Azam has to go now.
Commentary.Howout: b Ollie Robinson

OUT! TIMBER! There is the wicket England were looking for. An absolute jaffa from the legend! He has till got it. James Anderson, what a beautiful bowler. Mohammad Rizwan just stands there in disbelief as to how that ball went past his bat. What a delivery. Anderson serves a length ball, this one angling in and then moves away off the deck. Rizwan gets forward to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge and the ball goes onto hit the off stump. Just what England needed after the break.
Commentary.Howout: b James Anderson

We are back for the second session. 291 runs needed to win for Pakistan to level the series. A big session coming up for them. Here is James Anderson for the first time.
...Day 3, Session 2...

For the first time it feels, England were without any answer. The pitch has slowed up and the ball isn't doing much. It is a patience game really now. They are still on top of the game but the bowlers have to bowl much better in the next session and so on. They need to use more variations. England know a wicket or two and there will be nervousness in the Pakistani players' mind and they will look to bowl a lot better in the Post-Lunch session. Join us back at 1310 IST (0740 GMT) for all the action.

A terrific session for Pakistan. It couldn't have gone any better for them really. 5 wickets to start Day 3 with the ball and then they go into the break unhurt while chasing. They now need 291 runs to win. Still, a long way to go but this session helps Pakistan stay in the game quite clearly.
